Privacy Policy for BeHere

Effective Date: July 2026

Privacy Policy

Welcome to BeHere.

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it when you use the BeHere mobile application.

By using BeHere, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

Information We Collect:

1. Google Account Information

When you sign in using Google Sign-In, we may collect:

Your name
Your email address
Your Google account ID
Your profile photo (if available)

This information is used solely for:

Creating your account
Authenticating your identity
Personalizing your experience
Synchronizing your data across devices

We never collect your Google password.

2. App Data

BeHere stores information that you create while using the app, including:

Breathing session history
Meditation progress
Daily streaks
Goals
Preferences
App settings

This information is securely stored using Google Firebase Firestore.

3. Device Information

We may automatically collect limited technical information such as:

Device model
Android version
App version
Crash logs
Performance diagnostics

This information helps us improve the stability and performance of the app.

How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Provide and maintain the app
Authenticate your account
Save your progress
Synchronize your data
Improve app performance
Fix bugs
Respond to support requests
Protect against fraud and misuse
Data Storage

Your information is securely stored using Google Firebase services.

We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal information.

We do not rent your personal information.

We do not share your personal information with advertisers.

Your information is only shared with trusted service providers that are necessary to operate the app, including:

Google Firebase
Google Authentication services

These providers process data in accordance with their own privacy policies.

Data Retention

Your information is retained only as long as necessary to provide the services of the app or comply with legal obligations.

If you delete your account, we will make reasonable efforts to remove your associated personal data within a reasonable period, unless retention is required by law.

Children's Privacy

BeHere is not directed toward children under the age of 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

If we become aware that such information has been collected, we will delete it promptly.

Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the right to:

Access your personal information
Correct inaccurate information
Delete your account and associated data
Request a copy of your stored data

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information below.

Third-Party Services

BeHere uses the following third-party services:

Google Sign-In
Firebase Authentication
Firebase Firestore
Firebase Crashlytics (if enabled)
Firebase Analytics (if enabled)

These services have their own privacy policies.

Security

We use industry-standard security practices to protect your information.

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the Internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

Any changes will be posted within the app or on the page where this Privacy Policy is published.

The updated Effective Date will reflect the latest revision.

